# Backend work

Follow @docs/Reference/engineering/development/AI_AGENT_RULES.md and @docs/Reference/engineering/development/STANDARDS.md (especially the "Canonical Contracts" section — single source of truth for the response shape and helpers).

- Use existing patterns from @docs/Reference/engineering/development/RECIPES.md before improvising.
- Mirror a nearby service for structure (e.g. `complaint-master-service.ts`) rather than inventing a new layout.
- Controllers orchestrate only (validate → service → respond); business rules live in services.
- Before "done": run the gate in @docs/Reference/engineering/development/DEFINITION_OF_DONE.md (typecheck + lint + tests).
